		<h2 class='diff-currentversion-title'>Revision as of 21:06, 7 October 2014</h2>
<table class="infobox" style="width:22em;width:315px;float:right;clear:right;border-spacing:2px;font-size:90%">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:#B0C4DE;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle;font-size:110%">The North Saskatchewan Regiment</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align:center;text-align:center;font-size:90%;border-bottom:1px solid #aaa;line-height:1.5em"><a href="/wiki/File:N_Sask_R_Plain.svg" class="image"><img alt="N Sask R Plain.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/N_Sask_R_Plain.svg/300px-N_Sask_R_Plain.svg.png" width="300" height="300" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/N_Sask_R_Plain.svg/450px-N_Sask_R_Plain.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/N_Sask_R_Plain.svg/600px-N_Sask_R_Plain.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="567" data-file-height="567" /></a>
<div>Badge of the North Saskatchewan Regiment</div>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Active</th>
<td>3 July 1905–present</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Country</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Canada" title="Canada">Canada</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Branch</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Canadian_Army" title="Canadian Army">Canadian Army</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Type</th>
<td>Line infantry</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Size</th>
<td>One infantry battalion and one pipe and drum band</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Part&#160;of</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/38_Canadian_Brigade_Group" title="38 Canadian Brigade Group">38 Canadian Brigade Group</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Garrison/HQ</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Saskatoon" title="Saskatoon">Saskatoon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Saskatchewan" title="Saskatchewan">Saskatchewan</a> and <a href="/wiki/Prince_Albert,_Saskatchewan" title="Prince Albert, Saskatchewan">Prince Albert, Saskatchewan</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Motto</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Latin_language" title="Latin language" class="mw-redirect">Latin</a>: <span lang="la" xml:lang="la"><i>Cede Nullis</i></span> (Yield to none)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">March</th>
<td>"The Jockey of York" and, for pipe band, "<a href="/wiki/River_Avoca" title="River Avoca">The Meeting of the Waters</a>"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;background-color:#B0C4DE;text-align:center;vertical-align:middle;font-size:110%">Insignia</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Abbreviation</th>
<td>N Sask R</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row" style="text-align:left;padding-right: 1em;">Tartan</th>
<td>MacKenzie Hunting (pipes and drums only)<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The North Saskatchewan Regiment (N Sask R) is a <a href="/wiki/Primary_Reserve" title="Primary Reserve">Primary Reserve</a> <a href="/wiki/Infantry" title="Infantry">infantry</a> <a href="/wiki/Regiment" title="Regiment">regiment</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Canadian_Army" title="Canadian Army">Canadian Army</a>, headquartered in <a href="/wiki/Saskatoon" title="Saskatoon">Saskatoon</a>, <a href="/wiki/Saskatchewan" title="Saskatchewan">Saskatchewan</a>, with companies in Saskatoon and <a href="/wiki/Prince_Albert,_Saskatchewan" title="Prince Albert, Saskatchewan">Prince Albert</a>. Its current <a href="/wiki/Commanding_officer" title="Commanding officer">commanding officer</a> is <a href="/wiki/Lieutenant-Colonel_(Canada)" title="Lieutenant-Colonel (Canada)" class="mw-redirect">Lieutenant-Colonel</a> Tony Engelberts, who took over from Lieutenant-Colonel Dan Whittaker. The N Sask R is part of <a href="/wiki/Land_Force_Western_Area" title="Land Force Western Area">3rd Canadian Division</a>'s <a href="/wiki/38_Canadian_Brigade_Group" title="38 Canadian Brigade Group">38 Canadian Brigade Group</a>.</p>
<p></p>
